 Anti-Flag 成员向主唱 Justin Sane 发表声明：“操你，伤害了这么多人” https://www.nme.com/news/music/anti-flag-members-share-statement-to-frontman-justin-sane-fuck-you-for-hurting-so-many-people-3495012?utm_source= rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=anti-flag-members-share-statement-to-frontman-justin-sane-fuck-you-for-伤害了这么多人Will RichardsFri, 08 Sep 2023 07:32:44 +0000 Music NewsNews..Rock https://www.nme.com/?p=3495012 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="反旗" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>该声明是在本周有更多女性站出来指控萨内性侵犯之后发布的。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/anti-flag-members-share-statement-to-frontman-justin-sane-fuck-you-for-hurting-so-many-people-3495012">Anti-Flag 成员向主唱 Justin Sane 发表声明：“操你，伤害了这么多人”，该帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="反旗" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-getty-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>在本周有更多女性站出来<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/more-women-accuse-anti-flags-justin-sane-of-sexual-assault-3493583">指控萨内性侵犯</a>后，贾斯汀·萨内的前<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/anti-flag">反旗</a>乐队成员发表了一份声明。</p><p>针对萨内的指控首次浮出水面是在七月，当时一名女子在播客上声称自己被一名朋克歌手强奸，这名歌手最初没有透露姓名。反旗帜乐队<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/anti-flag-suddenly-split-without-explanation-3471204">随后解散，</a>但萨内后来发表声明，称这些指控“绝对是错误的”。</p><p>他的前乐队成员<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/anti-flag-share-statements-following-the-bands-sudden-split-3473859">就分裂和指控发表了一份单独的声明</a>，其中写道：“反旗帜乐队的核心宗旨是倾听并相信所有性暴力和性虐待幸存者的意见。最近对贾斯汀的指控与这一原则直接矛盾。因此，我们觉得唯一的直接选择就是解散。”</p><p>现在，在本周<a href="https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/anti-flag-justin-sane-1234817170/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>《滚石》杂志</em></a>的一份新报告中又有 12 名女性站出来指控 Sane 的虐待行为后，其他乐队成员——Pat Thetic、Chris Barker（又名“Chris 2”）和 Chris Head——通过电子邮件分享了一份声明，部分是针对他们的前乐队成员。</p><p> “根据<em>《滚石》</em>杂志最近发表的文章，我们要对克里斯蒂娜、詹、莫莉、丽贝卡、苏珊娜、马特、苏西、斯蒂芬妮、卡琳娜、艾拉、伊丽莎白、汉娜和塔莉表示感谢，感谢你们的勇气分享你所经历的痛苦，”他们写道。 “And, to others who may yet come forward, while you don&#39;t owe anyone your story, please know that you are not alone and that we believe you.”</p><p> Addressing Sane, they added: “To Justin, we believe you are very sick and in need of serious professional help. We want to have compassion and have faith in restorative justice, but fuck you for hurting so many people, not just the ones who have bravely come forward, but anyone still carrying their pain internally.</p><p> “Fuck you for exploiting the work of the band and the many people associated with it for so long. As many predators do, it appears you used our beliefs as a cover for egregious activities that you clearly knew we would never condone.” </p><figure id="attachment_3493601" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3493601" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3493601" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-justin-sane-stephen-j-cohen-getty-1.jpg" alt="Justin Sane of Anti-Flag" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-justin-sane-stephen-j-cohen-getty-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-justin-sane-stephen-j-cohen-getty-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-justin-sane-stephen-j-cohen-getty-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-justin-sane-stephen-j-cohen-getty-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-justin-sane-stephen-j-cohen-getty-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/anti-flag-justin-sane-stephen-j-cohen-getty-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3493601" class="wp-caption-text"> Justin Sane. Credit: Stephen J Cohen/Getty</figcaption></figure><p> The band&#39;s statement added: “To everyone, we collectively and individually still have far more questions than answers in this moment. We have been learning of and processing all of this information in real-time. We trusted Justin greatly and are now learning that we were deceived, lied to, and kept in the dark for the entirety of our association.</p><p> “As more details have been shared since the release of the podcast, we have been waiting for Justin to do the right thing. Given his lack of contrition in any meaningful way, it is very clear that he is absolutely not the person we were led to believe him to be.”</p><p> The <em>Rolling Stone</em> report published the accounts of numerous other women accusing Sane of sexual assault in incidents that date from the &#39;90s to as recently as 2020. Their accounts follow a similar pattern – Sane would allegedly make eye contact with them while performing and then approach them after the show. Many of these women claim they were much younger than Sane when these incidents happened, and the piece also accuses Sane having sex with teenagers. One of these incidents allegedly involved a 12-year-old (though Sane was a teenager at the time).</p><p> Some of the women allege that their encounters with Sane were violent and non-consensual. One of them is said to have reported an incident to the police, claiming Sane had handcuffed and assaulted her, in the UK in 2020. The woman involved said police had decided not to prosecute.</p><p> In a statement to <em>Rolling Stone</em> , the other Anti-Flag members said: “We trusted everyone associated with the band to maintain a safe and respectful environment. The understanding that abusers can be anywhere further reinforces the importance of survivors speaking out and sharing their stories.… Further, we feel strongly that all predators must atone for their inappropriate actions and be held accountable.”</p><p> Sane did not respond to requests for comment.</p><p><strong>如需有关英国性骚扰、攻击和强奸的帮助、建议或更多信息，请访问<a href="http://rapecrisis.org.uk/index.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener">强奸危机慈善网站</a>。 In the US, visit <a href="https://www.rainn.org/index.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RAINN</a></strong></p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/anti-flag-members-share-statement-to-frontman-justin-sane-fuck-you-for-hurting-so-many-people-3495012">Anti-Flag members share statement to frontman Justin Sane: “Fuck you for hurting so many people”</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
